				<div class="postbody">
				Nah.
<br />

<br />
I dont care about balance.
<br />

<br />
I just put a line about how I didnt care about balance and the fact chanters and rogue where weak in a balance way of thinking, then folks start arguing about what balance mean.  Balt was happy to jump on the balance arguing and trash me because he dont agree with the best definition about balance.
<br />

<br />

<br />
For some reasons peoples love to argue just to argue, while PvP alone is as just a setting could be for ''balance'', yet the strongest PvP toon, may have issue to solo or been group invited, which are differents topics and have very little to do with balance.  Exemple:  An awesome AE blaster can XP and kill easy mobs faster then anyone else and level quite fast, he may very well be the weakest toon as far as balance is, despite been the faster leveler.
<br />

<br />
Balance is not something desired or that should be seek by anyone, everything done in the name of balance is screwing a desirability factor of the class.  PvP is the only good way to measure ''balance'', but by no mean should you ''balance'' everything.  Balance talking was bringed about class who can and who cant solo, but...this is perfectly fine if not all class can solo, they will just not bother with this aspect of the game, it is not like if they didnt know they where unable to solo, of course the more you add for folks to be able to solo, the more options you give to players and the better, but it is perfectly acceptable that solo is restricted to only 1 class if you must(I would be playing that class automatically, so if you dont want overcrowding, you may want to diversify it so more then 1 class can solo, but you dont need every class to solo, the most raid wanted class could very well be completely unable to solo in anyform, while solo friendly class can very well be unwelcome in the raiding system(like mages)).
<br />

<br />
Anyway,  the main point of this thread is NOT about the definition of balance...you may agree with me or not, you can also agree with me when I think EQ, EQ2, WoW and CoH are all second generation MMORPG and by no mean a 3rd or a 4th like some peoples claim(3D mark a second generation while 2D is a first generation, in voice direct talking could be a 3rd generation), it hardly was the point of this message.  The main point of this topic was about a solution to make SOLO, GROUPING and RAIDING equally interesting in 1 game, rather then make a game where 1 aspect crush the others.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
